    "narrative": "Ghost Ride the WHIP enters today\u2019s slate prioritizing stolen base upside and favorable platoon splits to navigate a tricky pitching landscape. **Corbin Carroll** (87.14) is our unequivocal anchor; he draws a prime matchup against M\u00e1rquez (xERA 5.26) and benefits from the pitcher\u2019s glacial pace to the plate, which significantly boosts his already elite steal probability. Alongside him, **Seiya Suzuki** (68.49) offers a high-ceiling pivot against Roki Sasaki, with a +19% boost from the matchup and favorable wind conditions at his back. Meanwhile, **Brice Turang** (65.25) remains a staple at the top of the order; his elite sprint speed combined with a favorable leadoff spot against Mitch Keller makes him a must-start despite the neutral park factors.\n\nThe bench decision process was tightest at the corner infield spots, where **Max Muncy** (49.36) ultimately fell just short of a start. While **Muncy** possesses raw power, the optimizer favored **Josh Naylor** (60.52) for his superior situational positioning against Liberatore, despite the lefty-lefty disadvantage. **Austin Riley** also hovered near the threshold but was suppressed by a daunting matchup against Zack Wheeler (xERA 2.73), proving that our algorithm prioritizes schedule strength over name value. We are monitoring **Dalton Rushing**, **Alex Freeland**, and **Giancarlo Stanton** closely, as their scores are heavily dependent on confirmed lineup placement; any move down the batting order for **Rushing** or **Freeland** will further compress their marginal daily efficiency. Note that **Mickey Moniak** is officially ruled out due to a rainout, keeping our bench clean of potential dead weight for this cycle.",
